    <tr>
      <td style="vertical-align: top;">
      <h1 style="text-align: center;"><big>Tumblingdown</big><br>
      </h1>
Tumblingdown is a fast moving stacking game played on a checkerboard,
using more than the standard number of checkers.&nbsp; Your opponents
tallest stack is his "king", and your goal is to capture his king by
capping it with one of your pieces.<br>
      <br>
Tumblingdown was invented as an entry to a game design contest.&nbsp;
It was a finalist in the contest, but afterward was promptly
forgotten.&nbsp; It came to my attention
when someone pointed out the similarity of the move style to Exxit.<br>
      <br>
      <span style="font-weight: bold;">Robots:</span>&nbsp; Too tough
to beat reliably.<br>
      </td>
      <td style="vertical-align: top;"><img
 style="width: 591px; height: 374px;" alt="tumblingdown board"
 src="../images/tumblingdown-small.jpg"><br>
      </td>
    </tr>
